# Instructions for using SIREn

## Solr

The application is available at the address http://localhost:8080/siren/#/

The home of the Solr application is located at /etc/siren/solr.home/
and the schema of the index is found is a sub-folder, i.e., in the
file /etc/siren/solr.home/solr/collection1/conf/schema.xml.

## Update the schema definition

It is possible to change the schema of the index via the following steps:

1- Stop tomcat (either tomcat6 or tomcat7)
> sudo service tomcat6 stop

2- Edit the file /etc/siren/solr.home/solr/collection1/conf/schema.xml

3- Check the permissions (either tomcat6 or tomcat7)
> sudo chown tomcat6:tomcat6 /etc/siren/solr.home/solr/collection1/conf/schema.xml

## Logs

You can check the logs of the SIREn application by checking the catalina logs.

